Alstom, GE Shortlisted to Build Solar Power Plants in Algeria

-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 
2011-09-27T14:04:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/alstom-ge-shortlisted-to-build-solar-power-plants-in-algeria.html
     Sept. 27 (Bloomberg) --Alstom SA and General Electric Co.
are among companies shortlisted to bid for the construction of
solar thermal power plants in  Algeria , Algerian state utility
 Societe Algerienne de l’Electricite et du Gaz  said in Algiers.  Twelve groups of companies, which also include Alstom SA
and Spain’s SENER Ingenería y Sistemas S.A., will be invited to
participate in the tender before the end of this year, the
company announced at a bid announcement event today.  Ansaldo Energia SpA,  Germany ’s Flagsol GmbH, Cairo-based
Orascom Construction Industries and Italy’s CMS Industries were
also among the pre-qualified companies, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salah Slimani in algiers at 
 sslimani2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
